Title: Canonical quantisation of thermal gauge theories
Authors: P V Landshoff
Comments: 7 pages including one figure in pictex, DAMTP 93-55
\\
  Canonical quantisation gives a new and convenient finite-temperature
perturbation theory in covariant gauges, and solves the problem of the
zero-frequency mode in the temporal gauge. [Talk at Workshop on Thermal Field
Theories and their Applications, Banff, August 1993]
